I do not want to give into all the bias i have in my life. Seven different people telling me different stories. Seven different people trying to tell me what to do with my life, and who to be with, and what to do. Why can I not decide what I want to do with my life. It is my life, and I have more than me telling me what to do with it. MY LIFE, PLEASE LET ME LIVE IT TO THE POTENTIAL THAT I WANT.

ok before, that post.... listen to this one. 

Go to http://www.organdonor.gov to get a donor registration card, sign it, date it, and have two other people sign it. Carry it around with you in your wallet. If anything happens to you, your organs will be donated to someone in need.

You can also sign up with your state saying that you are an organ donor. There for is you dont have your card with you, they can still donate you organs. Go to http://www.livingbank.org/site/PageServer?pagename=homepage&JServSessionIdr003=2q8jgsprp1.app8b

I promise this page takes all of two minutes to fill out. Its not long at all. 

its simple, all you need is a pen, internet, and two other people with hands to sign something. No reason not to... its so easy. 


Print out a bunch, print out as many as you need and give them to people. Ask around, please try to get as many people to register!


thank you.

This is probably very rondom for most of you to read about in live journal, but it means alot to me, and other people who are in need of some sort of transplant. All i am asking you to do is become a organ donor. There really is no reason not to. If anything happens to you, you can save the lives of over 6 people. No one thinks that passing away can be a blessing to other families, or even someone in your family, but it truley is. You can no longer do it one your drivers liscence, but if you go to Texmed.org you can become a donor there. It is that simple. 

Over 3000 people die each year waiting for an organ transplant, and there are over 36,000 people waiting for one. If everyone would become a donor, these peoples lives would be saved by the loss of another. My Aunt was one of those people who died waiting for a liver transplant, which is why becoming a donor means so much to me. It is a simple task that doesnt take much effort, but in the end will be such a great gift to some one.  


That is all.

Texmed.org

go, and save the lives of people in need.
